No reason has been cited for the Wikify tag on this article.You can insert a reason using the |reason= parameter, like this: {{Wikify|reason=Your reason here}} Aldo Maria Brachetti-Peretti (born in Fermo on September 18, 1932), from a prominent family of the Marche, is chairman of an Italian company, API Group. Born in Fermo (Ascoli Piceno) September 18, 1932 from a prominent family of the Marche, after his degree in economics,[1][2] he began working in 1957 at API one of the major Italian oil downstream companies, while teaching economics and banking at the Universities of Rome and Parma.[3] In 1965 he joined the board of directors and in 1974 he was appointed executive vice president and CEO of API.[1] In 1977 he was appointed President and CEO. In 1978 he received the honor of "Cavaliere del Lavoro" from the President of the Italian Republic.[1][2] On October 6, 2009 he received an honorary degree in Engineering.[4] Presently he is chairman of api Holding S.p.A. and of Unione Petrolifera and one of the most important producers of Bordeaux style wines in Europe, with his own vineyard Il Pollenza.[5][6]
